post_text:
Dell Rapids High School and Middle School will be collecting items to benefit Veteran's Outreach next week. The list of the items for each day is listed below.

The Veteran's Day Program will be held on Friday, November 9th at 8:30 in the high school gym.

Monday - Paper goods (toilet paper, paper towels, facial tissue, napkins, etc)
Tuesday - Coffee supplies (coffee grounds, shelf stable creamer, standard size coffee filters, sugar)
Wednesday - Toiletries (disposable razors, shaving cream/gel, q-tips, deodorant, chapstick, foot powder, shampoo, body wash)
Thursday - Cold weather gear (sleeping bags, men's long underwear, snow boats (men's 9-11), hand/feet warmers, scarves, gloves (M-XL), hats (M-XL), winter coats (M-2XL), tube socks)
Friday - Laundry, cleaning and other (laundry soap, dryer sheets, dish soap, bath towels, bed bug spray, duffle bags)

REQUEST: I am the Chaplain at the Flandreau Indian School in Flandreau SD. Our students return to school in 2 weeks and our cross country season will kick off immediately. The request is--if you have any gently used shoes that you are no longer needing, would you be willing to donate to our program and our students? Many of our kids run in Converse or street shoes not realizing the difference a quality pair of shoes makes in a running performance--most just don't have the funds to buy a pair anyway. Greatest need is for Men's sizes 10, 11 and 12 although we can use whatever you've got. You can contact me through a FB message or my office # is 605-997-3773 xt 2175. I can pick up in the Sioux Falls area or you can ship to: FIS Chaplain,1132 N Crescent Street, Flandreau SD 57028. Thanks for anything you can send our way!
